00:12:05.680 --> 00:12:08.050 align:middle line:84%
that if we're going
to be teaching people

00:12:08.050 --> 00:12:11.530 align:middle line:84%
how to survive these types
of unconventional warfare,

00:12:11.530 --> 00:12:14.060 align:middle line:84%
it all comes back to physics,
biology, and chemistry.

00:12:14.060 --> 00:12:14.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:12:14.860 --> 00:12:16.780 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: So in
the Marine Corps,

00:12:16.780 --> 00:12:18.160 align:middle line:84%
you don't get sent
to university,

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:20.690 align:middle line:84%
you get sent to particular
training schools.

00:12:20.690 --> 00:12:22.810 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it was
at Fort McClellan,

00:12:22.810 --> 00:12:26.180 align:middle line:84%
which was an Army training
base in Anniston, Alabama.

00:12:26.180 --> 00:12:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And so they have their
own training systems.

00:12:30.550 --> 00:12:32.110 align:middle line:84%
But once I got out
of that training

00:12:32.110 --> 00:12:35.170 align:middle line:84%
to become a teacher
in this, I spent

00:12:35.170 --> 00:12:38.740 align:middle line:84%
a lot of my own time going
more deeply into the background

00:12:38.740 --> 00:12:40.763 align:middle line:84%
of physics, biology,
chemistry, and one thing

00:12:40.763 --> 00:12:42.430 align:middle line:84%
that I found while I
was in the military

00:12:42.430 --> 00:12:45.220 align:middle line:84%
and studying these
topics is that there

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:47.470 align:middle line:84%
were a whole series
of studies that

00:12:47.470 --> 00:12:52.610 align:middle line:84%
were based on geometric
aspects of physics, biology,

00:12:52.610 --> 00:12:55.600 align:middle line:84%
and chemistry that the general
public is not aware of.

00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:59.590 align:middle line:84%
We get presented with an image
of these modern sciences that's

00:12:59.590 --> 00:13:02.170 align:middle line:84%
almost completely
mathematical or algebraic.

00:13:02.170 --> 00:13:03.670 align:middle line:84%
And for the vast
majority of people,

00:13:03.670 --> 00:13:05.260 align:middle line:90%
that's very off-putting.

00:13:05.260 --> 00:13:07.183 align:middle line:84%
They're traumatized
by high school math

00:13:07.183 --> 00:13:09.350 align:middle line:84%
and they don't really want
anything to do with that.

00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:11.200 align:middle line:84%
And for example, I
found one document

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:13.690 align:middle line:84%
that was sponsored
by NATO and it

00:13:13.690 --> 00:13:17.470 align:middle line:84%
was a study of chemical
structures from a purely

00:13:17.470 --> 00:13:19.180 align:middle line:90%
geometric perspective.

00:13:19.180 --> 00:13:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this makes
everything so clear.

00:13:21.640 --> 00:13:24.160 align:middle line:84%
It's so easy to understand--
a child could understand

00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:28.250 align:middle line:84%
how these natural systems work
based on the geometry of it.

00:13:28.250 --> 00:13:30.190 align:middle line:84%
And over time,
what this led me to

00:13:30.190 --> 00:13:34.570 align:middle line:84%
was to study what the
geometric basis was

00:13:34.570 --> 00:13:38.020 align:middle line:84%
of modern physics,
biology, and chemistry,

00:13:38.020 --> 00:13:40.420 align:middle line:84%
and then to go back
into ancient traditions

00:13:40.420 --> 00:13:43.300 align:middle line:84%
and study what we think of
today as sacred geometry

00:13:43.300 --> 00:13:46.360 align:middle line:84%
and find one-to-one
matches between what's

00:13:46.360 --> 00:13:49.510 align:middle line:84%
been rediscovered today
in modern technology

00:13:49.510 --> 00:13:52.600 align:middle line:84%
as the patterns that all
of science is based on

00:13:52.600 --> 00:13:54.700 align:middle line:84%
and see how that was
known thousands of years

00:13:54.700 --> 00:13:56.770 align:middle line:90%
previously in other traditions.

00:13:56.770 --> 00:13:58.960 align:middle line:84%
And if I could give one
particular example that

00:13:58.960 --> 00:14:03.730 align:middle line:84%
was very affecting for me, I
was doing research, of course,

00:14:03.730 --> 00:14:07.960 align:middle line:84%
into the Egyptian and
the Pythagorean schools

00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:11.650 align:middle line:84%
and about the concepts of the
Platonic geometry, Archimedean

00:14:11.650 --> 00:14:13.010 align:middle line:90%
geometry.

00:14:13.010 --> 00:14:16.030 align:middle line:84%
And so this all goes back to the
perfect divisions of a sphere.

00:14:16.030 --> 00:14:18.790 align:middle line:84%
The sphere is the perfect
form in sacred geometry.

00:14:18.790 --> 00:14:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's because
the center, which

00:14:20.410 --> 00:14:24.730 align:middle line:84%
is our gateway to the
divine, has a boundary being

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:28.450 align:middle line:84%
created around it which becomes
the sphere of all of creation.

00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And for a sphere, the distance
between the divine center

00:14:32.860 --> 00:14:37.300 align:middle line:84%
and the periphery of creation is
equidistant in every direction.

00:14:37.300 --> 00:14:39.910 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes the
sphere the perfect form

00:14:39.910 --> 00:14:41.200 align:middle line:90%
in sacred geometry.

00:14:41.200 --> 00:14:43.510 align:middle line:84%
Every part of it is
equidistant from the divine,

00:14:43.510 --> 00:14:45.260 align:middle line:90%
from the center.

00:14:45.260 --> 00:14:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And so the next issue that
comes up in sacred geometry

00:14:48.580 --> 00:14:52.150 align:middle line:84%
is, how do you divide that
sphere into different forms

00:14:52.150 --> 00:14:54.790 align:middle line:84%
that have different
vibrational powers,

00:14:54.790 --> 00:14:58.023 align:middle line:84%
or what they would call sitas
in the Indian tradition.

00:14:58.023 --> 00:15:00.440 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So let me just stay
with you for a moment here.

00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:00.860 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: OK.

00:15:00.860 --> 00:15:03.193 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So are you saying
that all of the other forms

00:15:03.193 --> 00:15:06.233 align:middle line:84%
of geometry are essentially
embedded within the sphere?

00:15:06.233 --> 00:15:08.650 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: When you study the
particular pathway that was

00:15:08.650 --> 00:15:11.500 align:middle line:84%
taken in Greece, for
example, coming out of Egypt,

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:14.590 align:middle line:84%
then they really start with the
sphere and how do you divide

00:15:14.590 --> 00:15:17.290 align:middle line:84%
the sphere, but we don't always
explain what I just mentioned

00:15:17.290 --> 00:15:19.815 align:middle line:84%
about why do they always say
the sphere is the first form

00:15:19.815 --> 00:15:20.730 align:middle line:90%
of sacred geometry.

00:15:20.730 --> 00:15:22.770 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Which makes
perfect sense, of course.

00:15:22.770 --> 00:15:24.630 align:middle line:84%
Just look at the cosmos,
look at anything.

00:15:24.630 --> 00:15:25.720 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: Exactly.

00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:29.340 align:middle line:84%
And so the pathway they followed
again, coming out of Egypt,

00:15:29.340 --> 00:15:33.270 align:middle line:84%
was how do we then divide
the sphere into equal parts

00:15:33.270 --> 00:15:35.610 align:middle line:84%
that all have exactly
the same shape face, all

00:15:35.610 --> 00:15:37.642 align:middle line:90%
the same angles, et cetera?

00:15:37.642 --> 00:15:39.600 align:middle line:84%
And of course, there are
five perfect divisions

00:15:39.600 --> 00:15:42.312 align:middle line:84%
of the sphere that we
call the Platonic solids.

00:15:42.312 --> 00:15:43.770 align:middle line:84%
Now the thing about
it that I found

00:15:43.770 --> 00:15:46.290 align:middle line:84%
fascinating was in
the old Greek times,

00:15:46.290 --> 00:15:49.470 align:middle line:84%
they only made four
of those forms public.

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:52.290 align:middle line:84%
And the fifth form, the
form of the ether, which

00:15:52.290 --> 00:15:55.980 align:middle line:84%
is the dodecahedron, a 12-sided
form and every one of the faces

00:15:55.980 --> 00:15:59.340 align:middle line:84%
is a pentagon, that
form was kept secret.

00:15:59.340 --> 00:16:01.680 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we cannot
release this to the public.

00:16:01.680 --> 00:16:03.480 align:middle line:84%
The dodecahedron
has to stay secret

00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:06.240 align:middle line:84%
because if it was to
be misused as the key

00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:08.460 align:middle line:84%
to the ether, the
dynamic life force,

00:16:08.460 --> 00:16:11.280 align:middle line:84%
it could unleash incredible
forces of destruction

00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:13.450 align:middle line:90%
that people can't even imagine.

00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And so in the Pythagorean
school, and later

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:17.280 align:middle line:84%
Platonic schools,
you had to swear

00:16:17.280 --> 00:16:20.243 align:middle line:84%
you'd never make public
the form of the ether.

00:16:20.243 --> 00:16:21.660 align:middle line:84%
The only place
that you really see

00:16:21.660 --> 00:16:24.270 align:middle line:84%
it described by
Plato in his writings

00:16:24.270 --> 00:16:27.750 align:middle line:84%
is when he says that the
Earth, when seen from above,

00:16:27.750 --> 00:16:30.178 align:middle line:84%
looks like a 12-sided
leather ball.

00:16:30.178 --> 00:16:32.220 align:middle line:84%
And he's talking about
the dodecahedral structure

00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:33.450 align:middle line:90%
of the Earth itself.

00:16:33.450 --> 00:16:35.610 align:middle line:84%
Other than that,
it's very secret.

00:16:35.610 --> 00:16:39.060 align:middle line:84%
And so then I began to look
at declassified photographs

00:16:39.060 --> 00:16:39.960 align:middle line:90%
and documents.

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:42.090 align:middle line:84%
Do you actually go to the work
of people who are involved

00:16:42.090 --> 00:16:43.290 align:middle line:90%
with the Manhattan Project?

00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:16:43.740 --> 00:16:46.230 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: So for example,
Professor Robert Moon from

00:16:46.230 --> 00:16:48.570 align:middle line:90%
the University of Chicago.

00:16:48.570 --> 00:16:53.250 align:middle line:84%
He later made public a model of
the whole periodic table that's

00:16:53.250 --> 00:16:55.960 align:middle line:90%
based on pure Platonic geometry.

00:16:55.960 --> 00:16:59.190 align:middle line:84%
And so one particular
element is based on the cube,

00:16:59.190 --> 00:17:01.560 align:middle line:84%
another one is based on
the cube developing further

00:17:01.560 --> 00:17:02.880 align:middle line:90%
to the octahedron, et cetera.

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:03.910 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:17:03.910 --> 00:17:06.285 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: And so there are
these models of the periodic

00:17:06.285 --> 00:17:09.250 align:middle line:84%
table that's based on this
type of classical geometry.

00:17:09.250 --> 00:17:12.119 align:middle line:84%
And so I began to look for
declassified photographs

00:17:12.119 --> 00:17:13.670 align:middle line:90%
of the first nuclear weapons.

00:17:13.670 --> 00:17:16.069 align:middle line:84%
So I knew he was a part
of the Manhattan Project.

00:17:16.069 --> 00:17:19.260 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, also if you take
a look at Werner Heisenberg's

00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:22.079 align:middle line:84%
work, he's very much
about Platonic geometry,

00:17:22.079 --> 00:17:24.444 align:middle line:84%
and they're always dealing
with these ancient mysteries.

00:17:24.444 --> 00:17:26.819 align:middle line:84%
But these are only the most
advanced people in the field.

00:17:26.819 --> 00:17:29.410 align:middle line:84%
The average person doesn't
know anything about it.

00:17:29.410 --> 00:17:31.560 align:middle line:84%
And so as I looked at
declassified photographs

00:17:31.560 --> 00:17:34.530 align:middle line:84%
from the Manhattan Project,
I found these pictures

00:17:34.530 --> 00:17:38.250 align:middle line:84%
of what the actual interior
of the first nuclear weapon

00:17:38.250 --> 00:17:41.430 align:middle line:84%
exploded in Trinity Sands,
New Mexico actually look like.

00:17:41.430 --> 00:17:42.960 align:middle line:84%
Now what you normally
see, it looks

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:44.735 align:middle line:90%
like a sphere on the outside.

00:17:44.735 --> 00:17:46.110 align:middle line:84%
But if you take
off that cladding

00:17:46.110 --> 00:17:49.560 align:middle line:84%
and see what's inside of it,
it's a perfect dodecahedron.

00:17:49.560 --> 00:17:52.410 align:middle line:84%
And they said they had to
make the first nuclear weapon

00:17:52.410 --> 00:17:55.260 align:middle line:84%
in the form of a dodecahedron,
which they just described

00:17:55.260 --> 00:17:59.100 align:middle line:84%
as 12 pentagonal faces in
the declassified documents,

00:17:59.100 --> 00:18:01.230 align:middle line:84%
they said they had to do
that so that they acted

00:18:01.230 --> 00:18:04.560 align:middle line:84%
as radiant mirrors that
would allow the critical mass

00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:07.740 align:middle line:84%
to take place and for
the explosion to happen.

00:18:07.740 --> 00:18:09.150 align:middle line:84%
And when you see
that that's what

00:18:09.150 --> 00:18:12.870 align:middle line:84%
we have in modern times, and
that thousands of years ago,

00:18:12.870 --> 00:18:15.000 align:middle line:84%
from the Egyptian-Greek
tradition,

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:18.810 align:middle line:84%
they had warned that the misuse
of the dodecahedral pattern wow

00:18:18.810 --> 00:18:21.810 align:middle line:84%
could lead to incredible
