00:35:58.322 --> 00:35:59.280 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: Absolutely.

00:35:59.280 --> 00:36:02.980 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And these are very
simple subliminal ways in which

00:36:02.980 --> 00:36:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Steiner used in his
system geometry.

00:36:07.510 --> 00:36:08.650 align:middle line:10%
>> GILBERT: Absolutely.

00:36:08.650 --> 00:36:13.060 align:middle line:84%
So one particular anecdote from
Steiner's geometric work, which

00:36:13.060 --> 00:36:16.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm a huge fan of, I think it
was absolutely brilliant, he

00:36:16.840 --> 00:36:20.470 align:middle line:84%
had a private initiation
school from 1904 to 1914,

00:36:20.470 --> 00:36:22.750 align:middle line:84%
and then it ended with the
beginning of World War I.

00:36:22.750 --> 00:36:25.240 align:middle line:84%
But this went beyond what
he taught people publicly.

00:36:25.240 --> 00:36:28.600 align:middle line:84%
These were people that were
like his private initiate group.

00:36:28.600 --> 00:36:31.030 align:middle line:84%
And that material was
not available in English

00:36:31.030 --> 00:36:33.850 align:middle line:84%
until like the last
10 years or so.

00:36:33.850 --> 00:36:37.060 align:middle line:84%
It's only been very recently
translated into English.

00:36:37.060 --> 00:36:39.640 align:middle line:84%
And so you find some
fascinating things in there.

00:36:39.640 --> 00:36:42.580 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Was this during
his like Viennese period

00:36:42.580 --> 00:36:45.040 align:middle line:84%
in the coffeehouses where he
was starting to gather people

00:36:45.040 --> 00:36:46.930 align:middle line:90%
to him as a young man?

00:36:46.930 --> 00:36:49.560 align:middle line:84%
Was that in-- that must have
been in a relatively early

00:36:49.560 --> 00:36:50.360 align:middle line:90%
phase of his--

00:36:50.360 --> 00:36:52.943 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: It started in 1904,
so there's still some of that.

00:36:52.943 --> 00:36:55.150 align:middle line:84%
But he was beginning to
gain steam at that point.

00:36:55.150 --> 00:36:55.950 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:36:55.950 --> 00:36:58.607 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: And he was beginning
to have larger outlets.

00:36:58.607 --> 00:37:01.190 align:middle line:84%
And of course, that then led to
the building of the Goetheanum

00:37:01.190 --> 00:37:01.990 align:middle line:90%
in Switzerland.

00:37:01.990 --> 00:37:02.790 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, yes.

00:37:02.790 --> 00:37:04.390 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: And all
of that geometry.

00:37:04.390 --> 00:37:05.950 align:middle line:84%
But on this
particular trajectory,

00:37:05.950 --> 00:37:07.900 align:middle line:84%
looking at what he
was teaching people

00:37:07.900 --> 00:37:11.830 align:middle line:84%
about this very advanced form
of spiritual sacred geometry

00:37:11.830 --> 00:37:14.740 align:middle line:84%
in his private
initiation school,

00:37:14.740 --> 00:37:18.860 align:middle line:84%
there were debates that I
recall in the 1980s, 1990s

00:37:18.860 --> 00:37:21.520 align:middle line:84%
in modern metaphysics
about people

00:37:21.520 --> 00:37:22.820 align:middle line:90%
talking about the Merkabah.

00:37:22.820 --> 00:37:23.620 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:37:23.620 --> 00:37:24.940 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: And saying--

00:37:24.940 --> 00:37:27.250 align:middle line:84%
one particular line of
thought is, well, the Merkabah

00:37:27.250 --> 00:37:28.667 align:middle line:84%
is based on the
star tetrahedral--

00:37:28.667 --> 00:37:29.833 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right here, yeah.

00:37:29.833 --> 00:37:31.660 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: It based
on a six-pointed star.

00:37:31.660 --> 00:37:33.340 align:middle line:84%
And another person
would say, no,

00:37:33.340 --> 00:37:34.660 align:middle line:90%
it's based on the phi ratio.

00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:36.880 align:middle line:84%
It's based on a
five-pointed star.

00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:39.580 align:middle line:84%
And what you find in Steiner's
work is he-- it gives you,

00:37:39.580 --> 00:37:41.090 align:middle line:90%
once again, the larger context.

00:37:41.090 --> 00:37:42.410 align:middle line:90%
These are fragments.

00:37:42.410 --> 00:37:44.410 align:middle line:84%
And so what he
shows very clearly

00:37:44.410 --> 00:37:48.340 align:middle line:84%
is the classical teaching, which
is that the five-pointed star

00:37:48.340 --> 00:37:51.220 align:middle line:84%
is a form that actually
activates and works

00:37:51.220 --> 00:37:54.430 align:middle line:84%
in the circulation of
the human etheric body,

00:37:54.430 --> 00:37:57.140 align:middle line:84%
and the six-pointed
star activates and works

00:37:57.140 --> 00:37:59.350 align:middle line:84%
with the circulation of
the human astral body.

00:37:59.350 --> 00:38:03.640 align:middle line:84%
So they're both a part of a
much larger what we might call

00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:06.310 align:middle line:90%
Merkabah or Merkavah process.

00:38:06.310 --> 00:38:08.830 align:middle line:84%
But they're at different
planes, different levels.

00:38:08.830 --> 00:38:11.530 align:middle line:84%
And so once you start looking
at different planes of existence

00:38:11.530 --> 00:38:13.090 align:middle line:84%
and different human
subtle bodies,

00:38:13.090 --> 00:38:16.600 align:middle line:84%
the geometries change
for the different levels.

00:38:16.600 --> 00:38:18.970 align:middle line:84%
But that's not always explained
in the public material.

00:38:18.970 --> 00:38:20.740 align:middle line:84%
It's just like, why am I seeing
all these different patterns.

00:38:20.740 --> 00:38:21.540 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:38:21.540 --> 00:38:24.820 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: Sometimes they
align in another hidden way that

00:38:24.820 --> 00:38:28.750 align:middle line:84%
really becomes, once again, the
owner's manual for the initiate

00:38:28.750 --> 00:38:31.630 align:middle line:90%
to do highly precise work.

00:38:31.630 --> 00:38:34.720 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And in his
own work of the day--

00:38:34.720 --> 00:38:37.450 align:middle line:84%
and I would just bring this
up so people can go online

00:38:37.450 --> 00:38:40.300 align:middle line:84%
and take a peek at what the
original Goetheanum looked like

00:38:40.300 --> 00:38:43.300 align:middle line:84%
before it burned down, two
interlocking domes with no

00:38:43.300 --> 00:38:44.590 align:middle line:90%
visible means of support.

00:38:44.590 --> 00:38:45.920 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: Absolutely.

00:38:45.920 --> 00:38:51.250 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I went to his library
in Dornoch many years ago,

00:38:51.250 --> 00:38:54.040 align:middle line:90%
and talk about prolific.

00:38:54.040 --> 00:38:55.990 align:middle line:84%
Well, they were
essentially channelings.

00:38:55.990 --> 00:38:58.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he was just
streaming and downloading

00:38:58.630 --> 00:39:01.400 align:middle line:90%
this information to thousands--

00:39:01.400 --> 00:39:03.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there were
thousands of documents

00:39:03.280 --> 00:39:04.510 align:middle line:90%
that had come from him.

00:39:04.510 --> 00:39:07.990 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: And there's over 350
published books of either books

00:39:07.990 --> 00:39:09.288 align:middle line:90%
he wrote or collected lectures.

00:39:09.288 --> 00:39:11.080 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, collected
lectures as well.

00:39:11.080 --> 00:39:13.750 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a library full
of this, and I certainly

00:39:13.750 --> 00:39:15.730 align:middle line:90%
encourage anybody to begin--

00:39:15.730 --> 00:39:18.730 align:middle line:84%
what would you say to begin
with as a primal work of his

00:39:18.730 --> 00:39:20.770 align:middle line:84%
if someone was interested
in studying Steiner?

00:39:20.770 --> 00:39:22.270 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: That's
a great question,

00:39:22.270 --> 00:39:25.840 align:middle line:84%
because what I find in orthodox
Steiner circles is that they

00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:29.500 align:middle line:84%
tend to recommend these
extremely dense books that are

00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:31.570 align:middle line:84%
called the basic
books of Steiner.

00:39:31.570 --> 00:39:33.408 align:middle line:84%
And while they are
important, they--

00:39:33.408 --> 00:39:34.450 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: They're tough.

00:39:34.450 --> 00:39:36.410 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: They just
bounce people off of them

00:39:36.410 --> 00:39:38.170 align:middle line:90%
because they're so dense.

00:39:38.170 --> 00:39:41.620 align:middle line:84%
So like "Philosophy of Freedom,"
"Outline of Occult Science,"

00:39:41.620 --> 00:39:43.868 align:middle line:84%
brilliant texts,
but really dense.

00:39:43.868 --> 00:39:45.910 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not recommending
those as where to start.

00:39:45.910 --> 00:39:47.650 align:middle line:84%
That's what you tend to
get recommended if you go

00:39:47.650 --> 00:39:49.030 align:middle line:90%
to an anthropological outlet.

00:39:49.030 --> 00:39:50.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: What
would you recommend?

00:39:50.530 --> 00:39:53.000 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: I recommend a book
called "Founding a Science

00:39:53.000 --> 00:39:53.800 align:middle line:90%
of the Spirit."

00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:54.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:56.390 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: Which is a
series of lectures he gave,

00:39:56.390 --> 00:40:00.010 align:middle line:84%
which is extremely easy to
access and people can absorb it

00:40:00.010 --> 00:40:00.850 align:middle line:90%
very quickly.

00:40:00.850 --> 00:40:02.080 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: "Founding
a Science of Spirit?"

00:40:02.080 --> 00:40:02.440 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: Yes.

00:40:02.440 --> 00:40:04.450 align:middle line:84%
"Founding a Science of
the Spirit" by Steiner.

00:40:04.450 --> 00:40:05.680 align:middle line:90%
Great series of lectures.

00:40:05.680 --> 00:40:09.820 align:middle line:84%
And another one that's really
fascinating and very easy

00:40:09.820 --> 00:40:14.380 align:middle line:84%
to absorb is written
by someone who

00:40:14.380 --> 00:40:16.360 align:middle line:84%
attended early
lecture cycles of his

00:40:16.360 --> 00:40:18.800 align:middle line:84%
and was a writer,
Edouard Schure.

00:40:18.800 --> 00:40:23.200 align:middle line:84%
And Edouard Schure wrote a book
called "An Esoteric Cosmology."

00:40:23.200 --> 00:40:24.950 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: How do you
spell his last name?

00:40:24.950 --> 00:40:28.840 align:middle line:90%
>> GILBERT: S-C-H-U-R-E.

00:40:28.840 --> 00:40:31.800 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: No one would
have guessed that one.

00:40:31.800 --> 00:40:32.600 align:middle line:90%
Edouard Schure.

00:40:32.600 --> 00:40:33.892 align:middle line:90%
And the name of the book again?

00:40:33.892 --> 00:40:35.460 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: "An
Esoteric Cosmology."

00:40:35.460 --> 00:40:36.260 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:40:36.260 --> 00:40:38.468 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: In modern form,
sometimes they might just

00:40:38.468 --> 00:40:40.820 align:middle line:84%
attribute it to Steiner
because it's like straight from

00:40:40.820 --> 00:40:41.650 align:middle line:90%
Steiner's lectures.

00:40:41.650 --> 00:40:42.270 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right, right.

00:40:42.270 --> 00:40:43.550 align:middle line:84%
>> GILBERT: But these two
books, "Founding a Science

00:40:43.550 --> 00:40:45.680 align:middle line:84%
of the Spirit" and "An
Esoteric Cosmology,"

00:40:45.680 --> 00:40:47.900 align:middle line:84%
I find people can
absorb very easily.

00:40:47.900 --> 00:40:49.850 align:middle line:84%
And they're full of
fascinating insights.

00:40:49.850 --> 00:40:53.240 align:middle line:84%
So for example, in "An
Esoteric Cosmology"

00:40:53.240 --> 00:40:55.968 align:middle line:84%
is where they have the
summary knowledge about what

00:40:55.968 --> 00:40:58.010 align:middle line:84%
for the Rosicrucians does
the point in the center

00:40:58.010 --> 00:40:59.210 align:middle line:90%
of the circle mean?

00:40:59.210 --> 00:41:01.983 align:middle line:84%
Six-pointed star mean and
the five-pointed star mean.

00:41:01.983 --> 00:41:03.650 align:middle line:84%
I just talked about
the five and the six

00:41:03.650 --> 00:41:05.900 align:middle line:84%
related to the different
levels of subtle bodies.

00:41:05.900 --> 00:41:07.640 align:middle line:84%
There's another
level of it, which

00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:10.015 align:middle line:84%
is at the point of the center
of the circle they consider

00:41:10.015 --> 00:41:11.810 align:middle line:90%
to be the form of the godhead.

00:41:11.810 --> 00:41:14.270 align:middle line:84%
Then the six-pointed
star is related

00:41:14.270 --> 00:41:17.360 align:middle line:84%
to the form of the macrocosm,
and the five-pointed star

00:41:17.360 --> 00:41:18.950 align:middle line:90%
for the microcosm.

00:41:18.950 --> 00:41:22.730 align:middle line:84%
So very clear, concise
summary information.

00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:25.700 align:middle line:84%
Whereas in "Founding a
Science of the Spirit,"

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:27.200 align:middle line:84%
there's a discussion
where Steiner

00:41:27.200 --> 00:41:32.900 align:middle line:84%
talks about the forms
of the human astral body

00:41:32.900 --> 00:41:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and how this was
related at one level

00:41:35.180 --> 00:41:37.010 align:middle line:84%
to this egg-shaped
aura, like you

00:41:37.010 --> 00:41:38.720 align:middle line:84%
see in all the
theosophical paintings,

00:41:38.720 --> 00:41:42.470 align:middle line:84%
but at another level to the
six-pointed star structure

00:41:42.470 --> 00:41:46.430 align:middle line:84%
and to the activation of
particular nodal points

00:41:46.430 --> 00:41:50.270 align:middle line:84%
in the human energy body
related to a harmonic of three

00:41:50.270 --> 00:41:52.700 align:middle line:84%
and three nodal points
in the energy body

00:41:52.700 --> 00:41:54.470 align:middle line:90%
that the astral body roots in.

00:41:54.470 --> 00:41:58.580 align:middle line:84%
So in the head and the
heart and in the liver.

00:41:58.580 --> 00:42:02.360 align:middle line:84%
And so that three-fold division
of the soul is something

00:42:02.360 --> 00:42:04.580 align:middle line:84%
you find in many
traditions, but Steiner

00:42:04.580 --> 00:42:07.610 align:middle line:84%
has a particular way
of going into deeper

00:42:07.610 --> 00:42:09.270 align:middle line:90%
levels of these things.

00:42:09.270 --> 00:42:12.660 align:middle line:84%
And so again, as a
contextual knowledge,

00:42:12.660 --> 00:42:15.710 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the work
from the Rosicrucians,

00:42:15.710 --> 00:42:18.170 align:middle line:84%
they'll talk about the three
aspects of the human soul

00:42:18.170 --> 00:42:20.450 align:middle line:84%
being thinking,
feeling, and willing,

00:42:20.450 --> 00:42:23.000 align:middle line:84%
and with anchor points
in those three levels.

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:25.490 align:middle line:84%
But those same three levels
become the three Dantian,

00:42:25.490 --> 00:42:28.580 align:middle line:84%
in the three elixir fields
for internal alchemy

00:42:28.580 --> 00:42:32.150 align:middle line:84%
for the Chinese with the upper,
middle, and lower Dantian,

00:42:32.150 --> 00:42:33.380 align:middle line:90%
same areas.

00:42:33.380 --> 00:42:37.230 align:middle line:84%
For the Sufis, they talk
about the head, the heart.

00:42:37.230 --> 00:42:42.050 align:middle line:84%
And because in some
of the religions that

00:42:42.050 --> 00:42:45.080 align:middle line:84%
don't like to deal too much
externally with sexuality,

00:42:45.080 --> 00:42:46.850 align:middle line:84%
they don't talk about
the lower abdomen.

00:42:46.850 --> 00:42:48.920 align:middle line:84%
Instead they talk about
the metabolic forces

00:42:48.920 --> 00:42:51.320 align:middle line:84%
in the lower abdomen
expressing through the hands.

00:42:51.320 --> 00:42:53.960 align:middle line:84%
So for the Sufis, it's
head, heart, and hands.

00:42:53.960 --> 00:42:55.790 align:middle line:84%
So once you
understand the pattern

00:42:55.790 --> 00:42:57.380 align:middle line:84%
that they're all
based on, you can

00:42:57.380 --> 00:42:59.130 align:middle line:84%
see how all of these
traditions are really

00:42:59.130 --> 00:43:02.520 align:middle line:90%
talking about the same thing.

00:43:02.520 --> 00:43:04.500 align:middle line:84%
And so once you get
a pattern knowledge,

00:43:04.500 --> 00:43:07.190 align:middle line:84%
and that's the type of sacred
geometry as a divine language

00:43:07.190 --> 00:43:09.770 align:middle line:84%
that we were talking about,
if you have pattern knowledge,

00:43:09.770 --> 00:43:12.000 align:middle line:84%
you can study any
tradition in the world

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:15.467 align:middle line:84%
and you can see how the
pieces fit together.

00:43:15.467 --> 00:43:17.300 align:middle line:84%
Because one thing I was
always fascinated by

00:43:17.300 --> 00:43:19.510 align:middle line:84%
is when I studied
science, every year,

00:43:19.510 --> 00:43:22.970 align:middle line:84%
new discoveries in science are
integrated into the main body

00:43:22.970 --> 00:43:24.060 align:middle line:90%
of knowledge.

00:43:24.060 --> 00:43:27.380 align:middle line:84%
So they have to keep updating
the textbooks all of the time,

00:43:27.380 --> 00:43:29.820 align:middle line:84%
because we just learn something
new in biology, chemistry,

00:43:29.820 --> 00:43:30.840 align:middle line:90%
and physics.

00:43:30.840 --> 00:43:33.230 align:middle line:84%
But in metaphysics,
there tends to be

00:43:33.230 --> 00:43:35.330 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of "The
Lord of the Rings,"

00:43:35.330 --> 00:43:37.130 align:middle line:90%
my precious kind of thing.

00:43:37.130 --> 00:43:39.390 align:middle line:84%
Like this is my
body of knowledge.

00:43:39.390 --> 00:43:42.890 align:middle line:84%
And we-- new things come
out, new discoveries,

00:43:42.890 --> 00:43:46.600 align:middle line:84%
but we don't tend to unify
it into a collective body

00:43:46.600 --> 00:43:47.400 align:middle line:90%
of knowledge.

00:43:47.400 --> 00:43:51.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's where mature
metaphysics needs to get to.

00:43:51.090 --> 00:43:52.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:43:52.280 --> 00:43:55.640 align:middle line:84%
We can't have this protectionist
attitude towards something

00:43:55.640 --> 00:43:58.520 align:middle line:84%
that we feel we have
exclusive knowledge of.

00:43:58.520 --> 00:44:00.140 align:middle line:84%
That's not the time
for-- this isn't

00:44:00.140 --> 00:44:01.370 align:middle line:90%
the time for that anymore.

00:44:01.370 --> 00:44:02.690 align:middle line:90%
I agree with you totally.

